<br>
Well, I've been spending a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lot</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of time killing gnolls, and what I've found are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> three</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> lore scrolls, clearly marked as volumes 1 through 3, and another <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> tanned split paw skin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This fourth skin is different from the other three: it has a different icon <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (like a spell scroll or pattern)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, it is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> lore, and the text does not mention a volume number.<br>
<br>
Is this last scroll the fourth scroll, or is there really a volume four, lore, same icon as the rest, and marked as such in the text?  If so, is it exceptionally rare, or does it only drop deep inside <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Paw</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, or what?<br>
<br>
Not that I mind slaying <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Tesch Gnolls</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
